    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-04-09T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-04-09T23:00:00-05:00" n="602"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d602">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">693.113 (Manchuria) Petroleum/47: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-04-10T12:00:00+08:00"
                            >April 10, 1934—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received April 10—7:08
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>160. Department’s 85, March 30, 6 p.m. British Legation has had nothing from its
                    Foreign Office. American Consul General at Mukden<note n="87" xml:id="d602fn87"
                        >Myrl S. Myers.</note> reports however that his British colleague informed
                    him that advices from his Embassy [at] Tokyo indicate British Embassy proposes
                    to make similar representations in line with our suggestion. Myers expresses
                    belief that similar representations by American Embassy had become
                    desirable.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Tokyo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
